name: BoscoFace
content:
BoscoFace was a Lasat who appeared on a decorative poster, three years before the Battle of Yavin. Their name was printed on the poster, in Aurebesh characters. The poster, along with other illustrations, was used to decorate one of the crates at Zeb's Hideout, a cargo container at Chopper Base on Atollon, where fellow Lasat Garazeb Orrelios relaxed.
Later, when the infiltrator droid EXD-9 scanned Orrelios, the scan resulted in "SPECIES: LASAT" and "NON BOSCO FACE".
The name "BoscoFace" is most likely a reference to Bosco Ng, who directed the Star Wars Rebels episodes "The Mystery of Chopper Base" and "Warhead", in which the character's name appears.
